# 🪨📄✂️ Rock-Paper-Scissors AI Project

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.8+-blue?logo=python&logoColor=white)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Complete-brightgreen?style=flat&logo=checkmarx)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)
![Game](https://img.shields.io/badge/Game-Rock--Paper--Scissors-red?style=flat)

This project is a **Rock-Paper-Scissors game with an adaptive AI opponent**.  
It includes two modes:  
1. **AI Tournament Mode** – Your bot competes against 4 predefined AI bots over 1000 rounds each.  
2. **Human vs AI Mode** – Play interactively against the smart AI from your terminal.  

---

##  Features
- **Adaptive AI**: Uses pattern recognition (Markov chain) and special-case detection (e.g., vs Kris).  
- **Tournament Mode**: Your AI plays 1000 rounds against Quincy, Abbey, Kris, and Mrugesh.  
- **Human Mode**: Challenge the AI directly with your own moves.  
- **Modular Code**: Separated into `main.py`, `RPS.py`, and `RPS_game.py` for clarity.  
- **Beginner-Friendly**: Simple to run, well-documented, and easy to extend.  

---

##  File Structure
rock-paper-scissors/
│── main.py # Entry point with menu (Tournament or Human mode)
│── RPS.py # Your adaptive AI bot
│── RPS_game.py # Game engine + opponent bots
│── README.md # Project documentation

