## ▶ How to Run
Make sure you have **Python 3.8+** installed. Then:

```bash
# Run the project
python main.py
You will see a menu:

Enter 1 → Play Tournament Mode (AI vs 4 bots).
Enter 2 → Play Human vs AI Mode.

# Opponent Bots
Quincy → Cycles through [R, P, S, R, P].
Abbey → Predicts based on your 2nd-last move.
Kris → Random but skewed distribution.
Mrugesh → Plays your most common move in the last 10 rounds.

# AI Strategy (Your Bot)
Starts with fixed moves to gather data.
Detects if the opponent is “Kris” (counters your last move).
Uses Markov chain prediction to model opponent patterns.
Falls back to a cycle strategy if no data is available.

# Future Improvements
